Question
Hi guys,
so I have modified FEProblemSolve::solve() in MOOSE folder (/moose_beh/moose/framework/src/executioners/FEProblemSolve.C)
such that it moves on to the next step even if the simulation step isn't converged
bool
FEProblemSolve::solve()
{
  // This loop is for nonlinear multigrids (developed by Alex)
  for (MooseIndex(_num_grid_steps) grid_step = 0; grid_step <= _num_grid_steps; ++grid_step)
  {
    _problem.solve(_nl.number());

    if (_problem.shouldSolve())
    {
      if (_problem.converged(_nl.number()))
        _console << COLOR_GREEN << " Solve Converged!" << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
      else
      {
        _console << COLOR_RED << " Solve Did NOT Converge!" << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
        // return false;
      }
    }
    else
      _console << COLOR_GREEN << " Solve Skipped!" << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;

    if (grid_step != _num_grid_steps)
      _problem.uniformRefine();
  }
  // return _problem.converged(_nl.number());
  return true;
}

but I don't want this to be part of the main MOOSE code, I want MOOSE code to remain clean, and do everything in my own app.
I want to make a subclass that does exactly the same thing as, let's call it 'TransientMod'. How do I bring this modified FEProblemSolve::solve() into it?
I checked doxegen and i dont see the connection between  Transient.C and FEProblemSolve.C at all.
However, they are in the same folder (src/executioners) in MOOSE main src.
Kind regards,
Traiwit
